tissueExpression.summary: Normal tissues showed weak to moderate cytoplasmic staining. Neuronal cells of hippocampus, exocrine pancreas, rectum and stomach displayed strong positivity. Subsets of cells in seminiferus ducts of testis exhibited strong cytoplasmic and nuclear staining. Fallopian tube exhibited moderate cytoplasmic and membranous positivity. Bile duct cells, cells in glomeruli, endocrine gland, Leydig cells, smooth muscle, cardiac myocytes, glial cells and mesenchymal cells were negative. Detected at High or Medium expression level in 33 of 80 analyzed normal tissue cell types.

cellExpression.summary: Localized to the nucleoli & cytoplasm in both human and mouse cells.

tissueExpression.summary: Cancer tissues showed weak to moderate cytoplasmic staining. Occasional cases of malignant gliomas and ovarian cancers displayed strong positivity. Renal cancers were negative.
